HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 386
By Terry
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Providence
Christian Academy boys' basketball team,
TSSAA Division II-A state champions.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to specially honor and
commend those successful high school teams that, through their magnificent exploits, bring
honor to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors for this State; and
WHEREAS, the Providence Christian Academy (PCA) boys' basketball team achieved
an extraordinary level of success during the 2024-2025 season, winning its first ever TSSAA
Division II-A state championship; and
WHEREAS, the PCA Lions claimed their first ever Division II-A state championship in a
78-66 come from behind victory against the Battle Ground Academy Wildcats on March 8, 2025,
at the Hooper Eblen Center in Cookeville, ending their season with an exceptional 30-2 record;
and
WHEREAS, the 2024-2025 PCA Lions were led by Head Coach Kerry Hammonds, who
instilled in these exceptional young men a commitment to excellence in all that they do and
encouraged maximum effort on the basketball court; and
WHEREAS, state championships are achieved only through hard work, dedication, and
the ability to work together as a team and excel with a cooperative spirit; the Lions exhibited
each of these rare qualities during their championship season; and
WHEREAS, the young men of the PCA Lions realized an extraordinary achievement on
the court but also represented their school in a professional manner off the court; and
