WHEREAS, the dedication, determination, work ethic, and talent of these exceptional
young athletes steered them to the first ever TSSAA Division II-A state championship in school
history; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud the members of the
Providence Christian Academy Lions boys' basketball team for serving as exemplars of the high
quality of the student athletes of Tennessee; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the players, coaching staff, team support staff,
administrators, cheerleaders, and fans of the Providence Christian Academy boys' basketball
team on winning the program's first ever TSSAA Division II-A state basketball championship
during the 2024-2025 season.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
